 So the way that we think about quantum mechanics

30:41.200 --> 30:43.240
 is sort of as a generalization

30:43.240 --> 30:45.720
 of the rules of probability themselves.

30:45.720 --> 30:48.920
 So, you know, you might say there's a, you know,

30:48.920 --> 30:52.320
 there was a 30% chance that it was going to snow today

30:52.320 --> 30:53.160
 or something.

